info.senderName: NWS Jacksonville (Northeast Florida and Southeast Georgia)
info.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued February 26 at 6:41AM EST until February 26 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Jacksonville
info.description: ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM EST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Visibility below 1 mile in dense fog. * WHERE...Suwannee, Gilchrist, Southern Columbia, Western Alachua, Central Marion and Western Marion Counties. * WHEN...Until 10 AM EST this morning. * IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Areas of dense fog are moving across the Suwannee Valley and I-75 corridor from near Ocala to Lake City. Visibilities in the fog will vary greatly and may rapidly drop in normally fog prone areas like near Payne`s Prairie in Alachua county on I-75 and U.S. 301.
info.instruction: If driving, slow down, use your headlights, and leave plenty of distance ahead of you. Remain alert for rapid changes in Visibility.
